        <p>
            You've read the theory. You understand ethos, pathos, and logos. You can steelman an opponent's position, recognize a fallacy at twenty paces, and structure an argument that holds under pressure. Now you want to test yourself against real opponents, in real time, with real stakes.
        </p>

        <p>
            Welcome to SuperDebate—live debate clubs for adults, rebuilt for the modern world. This appendix won't teach you new rhetoric; everything you need is in the preceding twenty chapters. What it will teach you is how to deploy that rhetoric in the specific context of club competition: three-hour sessions, rotating opponents, community judging, and the camaraderie of people who take ideas seriously.
        </p>

        <p>
            The Greeks trained in gymnasiums before competing in the games. Consider this your orientation to the arena.
        </p>

